  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Australia Bushfires 2019/20</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">High temperatures and prolonged dry conditions have resulted in multiple bushfires in the states of New South Wales (NSW) since early November 2019, in Victoria (VIC), Western Australia (WA) and South Australia (SA) since early December 2019, and the Australian Capital Territory (ACT) in January 2020.
Over 30 people have died and over 17 million hectares have been burnt as a result of the bushfires. They have destroyed bush and farmland, and multiple towns. An estimated 4,200 residential and public structures have been destroyed. Loss of wildlife is estimated to have surpassed one billion, along with tens of thousands of livestock.</narrative>
  </description>
